{{Infobox artifact | name = Golden cup of Hasanlu | image = | image2 = | image_caption =Golden cup of Hasanlu, front and obverse sides | material =[[gold]] | size =height:21 cm diameter:21 cm | writing = | created = civilization before [[Medes]] | discovered = [[Teppeh Hasanlu]], [[Iran]] by Robert Dison | location = [[National Museum of Iran]] | id = }}
''' The Golden bowl of Hasanlu''' is a historical object made of gold. It was discovered by Robert Dyson in 1957 while excavating the site of [[Teppeh Hasanlu]], near [[Naghadeh]], northwest of [[Iran]]. The bowl is estimated to be around 3200 years or older.<ref name="1A">{{cite web |title=The Hasanlu Gold Bowl |url=https://www.penn.museum/sites/expedition/the-hasanlu-gold-bowl/ |publisher=Penn Museum |accessdate=17 September 2018}}</ref>
