Mounds]] || The Lake Ridge Island Mounds (also known as the Wolf Mounds I-IV) are a group of small hills in [[Logan County, Ohio|Logan County]], [[Ohio]], [[United States]], that have been thought to be [[tumulus|Native American mounds]]. Located in an area of about {{convert|5|acre}} at the northern end on Lake Ridge Island in [[Indian Lake (Ohio)|Indian Lake]], the mounds are near the village of [[Russells Point, Ohio|Russells Point]] in the southeastern corner of [[Stokes Township, Logan County, Ohio|Stokes Township]]. |- | [[Leake Mounds]] || [[File:Leake Mounds site 2015.JPG|125px|Leake Mounds]] || Leake Mounds is an [[archaeological site]] in [[Bartow County, Georgia]], built and used by peoples of the [[Swift Creek Culture]]. |- | [[Lewiston Mound]] || [[File:Lewiston Mound Jun 09.JPG|125px|Lewiston Mound]] || A burial mound located at [[Lewiston, New York]], in [[Niagara County, New York]], on the grounds of the [[Earl W. Brydges Artpark State Park]]. |- | [[Mann Site]] || || The Mann Site (12 Po 2) is located in [[Posey County, Indiana]], and was placed on the National Historic Register in 1974.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nationalregisterofhistoricplaces.com/in/Posey/state.html|title=National Register of Historic Places-Indiana, Posey County|accessdate =2009-12-31}}</ref> |- | [[Marietta Earthworks]] || [[File:MariettaMoundsOldDrawing.jpg|125px|Marietta Earthworks]] || Located at the confluence of the Muskingum and Ohio Rivers in [[Washington County, Ohio]], under the modern day city of Marietta. The site once consisted of at least four large platform mounds, three walled enclosures, and a large burial mound, now the site of the [[Mound Cemetery (Marietta, Ohio)|Mound Cemetery]].<ref name=ROMAIN1>{{cite book| author = Romain, William F. |title= Mysteries of the Hopewell |date= 2000-10-01 |publisher= [[The University of Akron Press]] | pages= 129–142 | isbn= 978-1884836619 }}</ref> |- | [[Marksville Prehistoric Indian Site]] || [[File:Marksville State His